-- Michael Page Won’t Have a ‘Fantastic’ Year, CEO Ingham Tells F&W
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2012-05-04T16:31:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/michael-page-won-t-have-a-fantastic-year-ceo-ingham-tells-f-w.html
Michael Page  International Plc Chief
Executive Officer Steve Ingham doesn’t expect a “fantastic”
year, Swiss newspaper  Finanz und Wirtschaft  reported, citing an
interview with the CEO.  Markets in  Spain , Italy and the U.K. are “difficult” and
business with financial companies is “sluggish,” Ingham was
cited as saying in an article to be published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at 
